  "prompt": "My iPhone screen broke I have iCloud, would notifications I received transfer over to a replacement or would contacts transfer and notifications gone?",
  "response": "If your iPhone screen is broken but you have iCloud enabled, your contacts and other key data should automatically transfer to a replacement iPhone when you log in with your Apple ID and restore from an iCloud backup. Here\u2019s a quick breakdown of what happens with each type of data:\n\n1. **Contacts**: Your contacts are stored in iCloud, so they will sync to your new iPhone as soon as you sign in with the same Apple ID and enable iCloud Contacts.\n\n2. **Notifications**: Notifications are device-specific and will not transfer to your new iPhone. Any notifications you received on your broken iPhone will be lost and won't be accessible after swapping to a new device.\n\n3. **Other Data**: Other data, such as photos, notes, and reminders, will also sync via iCloud, assuming you have those options enabled in your iCloud settings.\n\nTo set up your new iPhone:\n- Upon the initial setup, select the option to restore from iCloud and follow the prompts to log in with your Apple ID. \n- Make sure that your iCloud settings on the new device are set to sync the data you wish to have available.\n\nIf you haven\u2019t backed up your iPhone recently and are concerned about data loss, consider checking if your data is backed up to iCloud via the iCloud settings on your broken device (if possible).",
